issue.body:
Hey @pix3lot, I'm taking a look at #16 and it seems like I just had to rebuild the SlackItRevit.dll files. In the meantime, added a configuration for Visual Studio for Revit 2018 and updated the .gitignore file to prevent the Debug/obj or Debug/bin folder from being included.

I'll check with the issue creator to see if these files work for them now!
-Dan

issue.title: Adding pinned element tracking and GIF toggle
issue.body:
Incorporated pinned element tracking on load and just before sync, reporting as part of the syncing process. Currently looks at all model or annotation elements and compares a list of the two.

I had requests to disable Giphy integration, but I know it was a pretty hilarious part of the original idea, so I just created a new checkbox to toggle whether the GIF gets posted. If the box is checked, the GIF link is made null. This could probably be done in a better way so it's not making the request at all. 

Finally, I tried to get up .gitignore to leave the debug folders and temp files, but for some reason they still showed up. This should be removed since some are referencing local file paths.

Cheers!
-Dan Siroky

issue.title: Revit - other versions?
issue.body:
Really great tool, thanks for putting this together.

We have been experiencing issues with the addin not loading properly on machines that do not have Revit 2015 installed. 

![slackit error](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/30355499/28532293-69f75eac-7067-11e7-9950-8c650c03d88e.png)

If a machine has Revit 2015 + any other version installed (including 2018), it works fine if we copy/paste the dll/addin files to the Addin folder for different versions. But if a computer doesn't have 2015 installed, the error comes up. Once we install Revit 2015, it works again.

The simple fix is just to install Revit 2015, but we may be "losing" that version soon due to our licensing set-up. So wondering if there's something else we need to install to future-proof. Any help would be greatly appreciated.

issue.title: Get _start_state on DocOpen, regardless of settings
issue.body:
This should resolve #13, where someone opens a project and doesn't have pinned element tracking enabled, but then enables it and syncs. Since it previously didn't grab _start_state, the ReportChanges method would then fail due to a null _start_state.

I explored options of getting the _start_state when someone changes their SlackIt settings, but this would also have to account for receiving new changes via syncing the model. You'd also have to track the before and after save settings to see if it is enabled, which would add a layer of complexity. _start_state is already being updated every time you sync, so also doing so on document open is more in line with that pattern.
